35// Code to turn parameters to functions on stream into strings that
36// will be VLOG'ed. We need overloads, instead of
37// e.g. BatchDescriptorToVlogString(), as the code that calls these
38// functions does not know what the type of the parameter is.
39string ToVlogString(const dnn::BatchDescriptor &descriptor) {
40 return descriptor.ToShortString();
41}
42
43string ToVlogString(const dnn::FilterDescriptor &descriptor) {
44 return descriptor.ToShortString();
45}
46
47string ToVlogString(const dnn::ConvolutionDescriptor &descriptor) {
48 return descriptor.ToShortString();
49}
50
51string ToVlogString(const dnn::PoolingDescriptor &descriptor) {
52 return descriptor.ToShortString();
53}
54
55string ToVlogString(const dnn::NormalizeDescriptor &descriptor) {
56 return descriptor.ToShortString();
57}
58
59string ToVlogString(dnn::ActivationMode mode) {
60 return dnn::ActivationModeString(mode);
61}
62
63string ToVlogString(const dnn::AlgorithmConfig &algo_config) {
64 return algo_config.ToString();
65}
66
67string ToVlogString(dnn::ElementwiseOperation op) {
68 return dnn::ElementwiseOperationString(op);
69}
70
71string ToVlogString(dnn::QuantizedActivationMode mode) {
72 return dnn::QuantizedActivationModeString(mode);
73}
74
75string ToVlogString(blas::Transpose t) { return blas::TransposeString(t); }
76
77string ToVlogString(blas::UpperLower ul) { return blas::UpperLowerString(ul); }
78
79string ToVlogString(blas::Diagonal d) { return blas::DiagonalString(d); }
80
81string ToVlogString(blas::Side s) { return blas::SideString(s); }
82
83string ToVlogString(blas::ComputationType ty) {
84 return blas::ComputationTypeString(ty);
85}
86
87string ToVlogString(const void *ptr) {
88 if (ptr == nullptr) {
89 return "null";
90 }
91
92 // StrCat does not convert pointers to text.
93 std::ostringstream out;
94 out << ptr;
95 return out.str();
96}
97
98string ToVlogString(const HostBuffer &buffer) { return buffer.AsString(); }
99
100template <class T>
101string ToVlogString(const std::complex<T> &c) {
102 // StrCat does not convert std::complex to text.
103 std::ostringstream out;
104 out << c;
105 return out.str();
106}
107
108template <class T>
109string ToVlogString(const std::function<T> &f) {
110 return f == nullptr ? "null" : "<non-null function>";
111}
112
113string ToVlogString(const DeviceMemoryBase &memory) {
114 return ToVlogString(memory.opaque());
115}
116
117string ToVlogString(const DeviceMemoryBase *memory) {
118 return ToVlogString(*memory);
119}
120
121string ToVlogString(const Eigen::half &h) {
122 return port::StrCat(static_cast<float>(h));
123}
124
125string ToVlogString(int i) { return port::StrCat(i); }
126
127string ToVlogString(uint32 i) { return port::StrCat(i); }
128
129string ToVlogString(uint64 i) { return port::StrCat(i); }
130
131string ToVlogString(int64 i) { return port::StrCat(i); }
132
133string ToVlogString(float f) { return port::StrCat(f); }
134
135string ToVlogString(double d) { return port::StrCat(d); }
136
137template <class T>
138string ToVlogString(port::ArraySlice<T> elements) {
139 string str = port::StrCat(
140 ToVlogString(reinterpret_cast<const void *>(elements.data())), "[",
141 elements.size(), "]{");
142 const char *separator = "";
143 size_t max_to_show = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
144 if (!VLOG_IS_ON(2)) {
145 max_to_show = 5;
146 } else if (!VLOG_IS_ON(3)) {
147 max_to_show = 20;
148 } else if (!VLOG_IS_ON(11)) {
149 max_to_show = 1000;
150 }
151 for (size_t i = 0; i < elements.size(); ++i) {
152 if (i == max_to_show) {
153 str += ", ...";
154 break;
155 }
156 port::StrAppend(&str, separator, ToVlogString(elements[i]));
157 separator = ", ";
158 }
159 str += "}";
160 return str;
161}
162
163template <class T>
164string ToVlogString(port::MutableArraySlice<T> elements) {
165 return ToVlogString(port::ArraySlice<T>(elements));
166}

168string ToVlogString(dnn::DepthToSpaceLayout depth_to_space_layout) {
169 switch (depth_to_space_layout) {
170 case dnn::DepthToSpaceLayout::DepthHeightWidth:
171 return "DepthToSpaceLayout::DepthHeightWidth";
172 }
173 return "unknown DepthToSpaceLayout";
174}
175
176string ToVlogString(dnn::DataType data_type) {
177 switch (data_type) {
178 case dnn::DataType::kFloat:
179 return "dnn::DataType::kFloat";
180 case dnn::DataType::kDouble:
181 return "dnn::DataType::kDouble";
182 case dnn::DataType::kHalf:
183 return "dnn::DataType::kHalf";
184 case dnn::DataType::kInt8:
185 return "dnn::DataType::kInt8";
186 }
187}
188
189// Used together with PARAM to VLOG calls made to the stream. Intended
190// to be used like this:
191//
192// VLOG(1) << CallStr("MyFunction", this, {PARAM(a), PARAM(b)});
193//
194// where a and b are the parameters to MyFunction.
195//
196// See VLOG_CALL for a short-hand for this. This way of doing it saves
197// a tremendous amount of boilerplate code given how many functions
198// there are on Stream and how many parameters they each have.
199string CallStr(const char *function_name, Stream *stream,
200 std::vector<std::pair<const char *, string>> params) {
201 // Do not call this function unless VLOG is on since just
202 // constructing all the strings in params is expensive.
203 CHECK(VLOG_IS_ON(1));
204
205 string str = port::StrCat("Called Stream::", function_name, "(");
206 const char *separator = "";
207 for (const auto &param : params) {
208 port::StrAppend(&str, separator, param.first, "=", param.second);
209 separator = ", ";
210 }
211 port::StrAppend(&str, ") stream=", ToVlogString(stream));
212 if (VLOG_IS_ON(10)) {
213 port::StrAppend(&str, " ", port::CurrentStackTrace(), "\n");
214 }
215 return str;
216}
217
218// Use this macro to avoid having to type every parameter twice to log
219// it with VLOG and CallStr.
220#define PARAM(parameter) \
221 { #parameter, ToVlogString(parameter) }
222
223// Use this macro to avoid having to type out the name of each
224// function and to save some boilerplate. Intended to be used like this:
225//
226// VLOG_CALL(PARAM(a), PARAM(b))
227//
228// This saves a tremendous amount of boilerplate compared to the alternative:
229//
230// VLOG(1) << "Calling MyFunction(a=" << ToVlogString(a)
231// << ", b=" << ToVlogString(b);
232//
233// Note here that most of the parameter names are not short and that
234// most of the functions take many more than 2 parameters.
235#define VLOG_CALL(...) VLOG(1) << CallStr(__func__, this, {__VA_ARGS__})
236
237} // namespace

239Stream::Stream(StreamExecutor *parent)
240 : parent_(parent),
241 implementation_(parent->implementation()->GetStreamImplementation()),
242 allocated_(false),
243 ok_(false),
244 temporary_memory_manager_(this) {
245 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(parent));
246}
247
248Stream::Stream(StreamExecutor *parent,
249 internal::StreamInterface *implementation)
250 : parent_(parent),
251 implementation_(implementation),
252 allocated_(false),
253 ok_(false),
254 temporary_memory_manager_(this) {
255 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(parent), PARAM(implementation));
256}
257
258Stream::~Stream() {
259 VLOG_CALL();
260
261 temporary_memory_manager_.ForceDeallocateAll();
262
263 if (allocated_) {
264 parent_->DeallocateStream(this);
265 }
266}
267
268Stream &Stream::Init() {
269 VLOG_CALL();
270
271 mutex_lock lock{mu_};
272 CHECK_EQ(false, allocated_)
273 << "stream appears to already have been initialized";
274 CHECK(!ok_) << "stream should be in !ok() state pre-initialization";
275
276 if (parent_->AllocateStream(this)) {
277 // Successful initialization!
278 allocated_ = true;
279 ok_ = true;
280 } else {
281 LOG(ERROR) << "failed to allocate stream during initialization";
282 }
283
284 return *this;
285}
286
287Stream &Stream::InitTimer(Timer *timer) {
288 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(timer));
289
290 if (ok()) {
291 CheckError(parent_->AllocateTimer(timer));
292 } else {
293 LOG(INFO) << "did not allocate timer: " << timer;
294 }
295 return *this;
296}
297
298Stream &Stream::InitWithTimer(Timer *timer) {
299 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(timer));
300
301 return Init().InitTimer(timer);
302}
303
304Stream &Stream::ThenRecordEvent(Event *event) {
305 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(event));
306
307 port::Status status = parent_->RecordEvent(this, event);
308 if (!status.ok()) {
309 LOG(ERROR) << "Error recording event in stream: " << status.error_message()
310 << "; not marking stream as bad, as the Event object may be "
311 << "at fault. Monitor for further errors.";
312 }
313
314 return *this;
315}

317Stream &Stream::ThenBatchNormalizationForward(
318 const DeviceMemory<float> &x, const DeviceMemory<float> &scale,
319 const DeviceMemory<float> &offset,
320 const DeviceMemory<float> &estimated_mean,
321 const DeviceMemory<float> &estimated_variance,
322 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &x_desc,
323 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &scale_offset_desc, const double epsilon,
324 DeviceMemory<float> *y, DeviceMemory<float> *batch_mean,
325 DeviceMemory<float> *batch_var, DeviceMemory<float> *saved_mean,
326 DeviceMemory<float> *saved_inv_var, bool is_training,
327 std::function<const DeviceMemory<float> &()> var_to_inv_var,
328 std::function<void()> inv_var_to_var) {
329 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(x), PARAM(scale), PARAM(offset), PARAM(x_desc),
330 PARAM(scale_offset_desc), PARAM(epsilon), PARAM(y));
331 if (ok()) {
332 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
333 CheckError(dnn->DoBatchNormalizationForward(
334 this, x, scale, offset, estimated_mean, estimated_variance, x_desc,
335 scale_offset_desc, epsilon, y, batch_mean, batch_var, saved_mean,
336 saved_inv_var, is_training, std::move(var_to_inv_var),
337 std::move(inv_var_to_var)));
338 } else {
339 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
340 }
341 }
342 return *this;
343}

345Stream &Stream::ThenBatchNormalizationBackward(
346 const DeviceMemory<float> &y_backprop, const DeviceMemory<float> &x,
347 const DeviceMemory<float> &scale, const DeviceMemory<float> &mean,
348 const DeviceMemory<float> &inv_var, const dnn::BatchDescriptor &x_desc,
349 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &scale_offset_desc, const double epsilon,
350 DeviceMemory<float> *x_backprop, DeviceMemory<float> *scale_backprop,
351 DeviceMemory<float> *offset_backprop) {
352 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(y_backprop), PARAM(x), PARAM(scale), PARAM(x_desc),
353 PARAM(scale_offset_desc), PARAM(epsilon), PARAM(x_backprop),
354 PARAM(scale_backprop), PARAM(offset_backprop));
355 if (ok()) {
356 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
357 CheckError(dnn->DoBatchNormalizationBackward(
358 this, y_backprop, x, scale, mean, inv_var, x_desc, scale_offset_desc,
359 epsilon, x_backprop, scale_backprop, offset_backprop));
360 } else {
361 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
362 }
363 }
364 return *this;
365}

418Stream &Stream::ThenFusedConvolveWithScratch(
419 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &conv_input_descriptor,
420 const DeviceMemory<int8> &conv_input_data, float conv_input_scale,
421 const dnn::FilterDescriptor &filter_descriptor,
422 const DeviceMemory<int8> &filter_data,
423 const dnn::ConvolutionDescriptor &convolution_descriptor,
424 const DeviceMemory<int8> &side_input_data, float side_input_scale,
425 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &bias_descriptor,
426 const DeviceMemory<float> &biases, dnn::ActivationMode activation_mode,
427 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &output_descriptor, DeviceMemory<int8> *output,
428 ScratchAllocator *scratch_allocator) {
429 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(conv_input_descriptor), PARAM(conv_input_data),
430 PARAM(conv_input_scale), PARAM(filter_descriptor),
431 PARAM(filter_data), PARAM(convolution_descriptor),
432 PARAM(side_input_data), PARAM(side_input_scale),
433 PARAM(bias_descriptor), PARAM(biases), PARAM(activation_mode),
434 PARAM(output_descriptor), PARAM(output));
435
436 if (ok()) {
437 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
438 CheckError(dnn->DoFusedConvolve(
439 this, conv_input_descriptor, conv_input_data, conv_input_scale,
440 filter_descriptor, filter_data, convolution_descriptor,
441 side_input_data, side_input_scale, bias_descriptor, biases,
442 activation_mode, output_descriptor, output, scratch_allocator,
443 dnn::AlgorithmConfig(), /*output_profile_result=*/nullptr));
444 } else {
445 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
446 }
447 }
448 return *this;
449}

572Stream &Stream::ThenFusedConvolveWithAlgorithm(
573 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &conv_input_descriptor,
574 const DeviceMemory<float> &conv_input_data, float conv_input_scale,
575 const dnn::FilterDescriptor &filter_descriptor,
576 const DeviceMemory<float> &filter_data,
577 const dnn::ConvolutionDescriptor &convolution_descriptor,
578 const DeviceMemory<float> &side_input_data, float side_input_scale,
579 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &bias_descriptor,
580 const DeviceMemory<float> &biases, dnn::ActivationMode activation_mode,
581 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &output_descriptor, DeviceMemory<float> *output,
582 ScratchAllocator *scratch_allocator,
583 const dnn::AlgorithmConfig &algorithm_config,
584 dnn::ProfileResult *output_profile_result) {
585 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(conv_input_descriptor), PARAM(conv_input_data),
586 PARAM(conv_input_scale), PARAM(filter_descriptor),
587 PARAM(filter_data), PARAM(convolution_descriptor), PARAM(biases),
588 PARAM(side_input_data), PARAM(side_input_scale),
589 PARAM(activation_mode), PARAM(output_descriptor), PARAM(output),
590 PARAM(algorithm_config));
591
592 if (ok()) {
593 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
594 auto status = dnn->DoFusedConvolve(
595 this, conv_input_descriptor, conv_input_data, conv_input_scale,
596 filter_descriptor, filter_data, convolution_descriptor,
597 side_input_data, side_input_scale, bias_descriptor, biases,
598 activation_mode, output_descriptor, output, scratch_allocator,
599 algorithm_config, output_profile_result);
600 if (!status && !output_profile_result) {
601 SetError();
602 }
603 } else {
604 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
605 }
606 }
607 return *this;
608}

610Stream &Stream::ThenFusedConvolveWithAlgorithm(
611 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &conv_input_descriptor,
612 const DeviceMemory<Eigen::half> &conv_input_data, float conv_input_scale,
613 const dnn::FilterDescriptor &filter_descriptor,
614 const DeviceMemory<Eigen::half> &filter_data,
615 const dnn::ConvolutionDescriptor &convolution_descriptor,
616 const DeviceMemory<Eigen::half> &side_input_data, float side_input_scale,
617 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &bias_descriptor,
618 const DeviceMemory<Eigen::half> &biases,
619 dnn::ActivationMode activation_mode,
620 const dnn::BatchDescriptor &output_descriptor,
621 DeviceMemory<Eigen::half> *output, ScratchAllocator *scratch_allocator,
622 const dnn::AlgorithmConfig &algorithm_config,
623 dnn::ProfileResult *output_profile_result) {
624 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(conv_input_descriptor), PARAM(conv_input_data),
625 PARAM(conv_input_scale), PARAM(filter_descriptor),

1590Stream &Stream::ThenDepthConcatenate(
1591 port::ArraySlice<dnn::BatchDescriptor> input_dimensions,
1592 port::ArraySlice<const DeviceMemory<float> *> input_data,
1593 DeviceMemory<float> *output_data) {
1594 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(input_dimensions), PARAM(input_data), PARAM(output_data));
1595
1596 for (size_t i = 1; i < input_dimensions.size(); ++i) {
1597 if (input_dimensions[i].count() != input_dimensions[0].count() ||
1598 input_dimensions[i].height() != input_dimensions[0].height() ||
1599 input_dimensions[i].width() != input_dimensions[0].width()) {
1600 SetError();
1601 LOG(ERROR) << "Incompatible dimensions for depth concatenation.\n"
1602 << "input_dimensions[0]: " << input_dimensions[0].ToString()
1603 << "input_dimensions[" << i
1604 << "]: " << input_dimensions[i].ToString();
1605 return *this;
1606 }
1607 }
1608
1609 if (ok()) {
1610 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
1611 CheckError(dnn->DoDepthConcatenate(this, input_dimensions, input_data,
1612 output_data));
1613 } else {
1614 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
1615 }
1616 }
1617 return *this;
1618}
1619
1620Stream &Stream::ThenSpaceConcatenate(
1621 port::ArraySlice<dnn::BatchDescriptor> input_dimensions,
1622 port::ArraySlice<const DeviceMemory<float> *> input_data,
1623 DeviceMemory<float> *output_data,
1624 dnn::SpaceConcatenateMode concat_direction) {
1625 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(input_dimensions), PARAM(input_data), PARAM(output_data));
1626
1627 // Check that the input dimensions of all the other batches match those of the
1628 // first batch.
1629 for (size_t i = 1; i < input_dimensions.size(); ++i) {
1630 if ((concat_direction == dnn::SpaceConcatenateMode::XDirection) &&
1631 (input_dimensions[i].count() != input_dimensions[0].count() ||
1632 input_dimensions[i].height() != input_dimensions[0].height() ||
1633 input_dimensions[i].feature_map_count() !=
1634 input_dimensions[0].feature_map_count())) {
1635 SetError();
1636 LOG(ERROR) << "Incompatible dimensions for X concatenation.\n"
1637 << "input_dimensions[0]: " << input_dimensions[0].ToString()
1638 << "input_dimensions[" << i
1639 << "]: " << input_dimensions[i].ToString();
1640 return *this;
1641 }
1642
1643 if ((concat_direction == dnn::SpaceConcatenateMode::YDirection) &&
1644 (input_dimensions[i].count() != input_dimensions[0].count() ||
1645 input_dimensions[i].width() != input_dimensions[0].width() ||
1646 input_dimensions[i].feature_map_count() !=
1647 input_dimensions[0].feature_map_count())) {
1648 SetError();
1649 LOG(ERROR) << "Incompatible dimensions for Y concatenation.\n"
1650 << "input_dimensions[0]: " << input_dimensions[0].ToString()
1651 << "input_dimensions[" << i
1652 << "]: " << input_dimensions[i].ToString();
1653 return *this;
1654 }
1655 }
1656 if (ok()) {
1657 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
1658 CheckError(dnn->DoSpaceConcatenate(this, input_dimensions, input_data,
1659 output_data, concat_direction));
1660 } else {
1661 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
1662 }
1663 }
1664 return *this;
1665}

1831 dnn::QuantizedActivationMode mode, void *host_dst, uint64 size) {
1832 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(gpu_unquantized_src), PARAM(mode), PARAM(host_dst),
1833 PARAM(size));
1834
1835 if (ok()) {
1836 if (dnn::DnnSupport *dnn = parent_->AsDnn()) {
1837 CheckError(dnn->DoMemcpyD2HQuantized(this, gpu_unquantized_src, mode,
1838 host_dst, size));
1839 } else {
1840 SetErrorAndLogNoDnnSupport();
1841 }
1842 }
1843 return *this;
1844}

1892
1893Stream *Stream::GetOrCreateSubStream() {
1894 mutex_lock lock{mu_};
1895 for (auto &stream : sub_streams_) {
1896 if (stream.second) {
1897 stream.second = false;
1898 return stream.first.get();
1899 }
1900 }
1901 sub_streams_.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<Stream>{new Stream{parent_}},
1902 false);
1903 Stream *sub_stream = sub_streams_.back().first.get();
1904 sub_stream->Init();
1905 CHECK(ok_) << "sub-stream failed to be initialized";
1906
1907 return sub_stream;
1908}
1909
1910void Stream::ReturnSubStream(Stream *sub_stream) {
1911 mutex_lock lock{mu_};
1912 for (auto &stream : sub_streams_) {
1913 if (stream.first.get() == sub_stream) {
1914 stream.second = true;
1915 return;
1916 }
1917 }
1918 LOG(FATAL) << "the sub-stream to be returned is not created by this stream";
1919}
1920
1921Stream &Stream::ThenStartTimer(Timer *t) {
1922 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(t));
1923
1924 if (ok()) {
1925 CheckError(parent_->StartTimer(this, t));
1926 } else {
1927 LOG(INFO) << "stream " << this << " did not enqueue 'start timer': " << t;
1928 }
1929 return *this;
1930}
1931
1932Stream &Stream::ThenStopTimer(Timer *t) {
1933 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(t));
1934
1935 if (ok()) {
1936 CheckError(parent_->StopTimer(this, t));
1937 } else {
1938 LOG(INFO) << "stream " << this << " did not enqueue 'stop timer': " << t;
1939 }
1940 return *this;
1941}
1942
1943Stream &Stream::ThenWaitFor(Stream *other) {
1944 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(other));
1945
1946 CHECK(this != other) << "stream cannot wait for itself";
1947 if (ok() && other->ok()) {
1948 CheckError(parent_->CreateStreamDependency(this, other));
1949 } else {
1950 SetError();
1951 LOG(INFO) << "stream " << this << " did not wait for stream: " << other;
1952 }
1953 return *this;
1954}
1955
1956Stream &Stream::ThenWaitFor(Event *event) {
1957 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(event));
1958
1959 if (ok()) {
1960 port::Status status = parent_->WaitForEvent(this, event);
1961 if (!status.ok()) {
1962 LOG(ERROR) << "Error waiting for event in stream: "
1963 << status.error_message()
1964 << "; not marking stream as bad, as the Event object may be "
1965 << "at fault. Monitor for further errors.";
1966 }
1967 } else {
1968 LOG(INFO) << "stream " << this << " did not wait for an event.";
1969 }
1970 return *this;
1971}
1972
1973// A functor that implements ThenBlasXXX interfaces, which calls DoBlasXXX
1974// functions and logs for errors.
1975template <typename... Args>
1976struct ThenBlasImpl {
1977 // blas_func is the DoBlasXXX member function pointer, and args are its
1978 // arguments except the first one of Stream* type.
1979 Stream &operator()(Stream *stream,
1980 bool (blas::BlasSupport::*blas_func)(Stream *, Args...),
1981 Args... args) {
1982 return Run(stream, blas_func, /*record_error=*/true, args...);
1983 }
1984
1985 // Like operator(), but only calls stream->CheckError() if record_error is
1986 // true.
1987 Stream &Run(Stream *stream,
1988 bool (blas::BlasSupport::*blas_func)(Stream *, Args...),
1989 bool record_error, Args... args);
1990};
1991
1992template <typename... Args>
1993Stream &ThenBlasImpl<Args...>::Run(
1994 Stream *stream, bool (blas::BlasSupport::*blas_func)(Stream *, Args...),
1995 bool record_error, Args... args) {
1996 if (stream->ok()) {
1997 bool ok;
1998 if (blas::BlasSupport *blas = stream->parent_->AsBlas()) {
1999 ok = (blas->*blas_func)(stream, args...);
2000 } else {
2001 LOG(WARNING)
2002 << "attempting to perform BLAS operation using StreamExecutor "
2003 "without BLAS support";
2004 ok = false;
2005 }
2006 if (record_error) {
2007 stream->CheckError(ok);
2008 }
2009 }
2010 return *stream;
2011}

2013Stream &Stream::ThenBlasAsum(uint64 elem_count, const DeviceMemory<float> &x,
2014 int incx, DeviceMemory<float> *result) {
2015 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(elem_count), PARAM(x), PARAM(incx), PARAM(result));
2016
2017 ThenBlasImpl<uint64, const DeviceMemory<float> &, int, DeviceMemory<float> *>
2018 impl;
2019 return impl(this, &blas::BlasSupport::DoBlasAsum, elem_count, x, incx,
2020 result);
2021}

3687
3688namespace {
3689// Like ThenBlasImpl, except this expects the last argument of blas_func to be a
3690// blas::ProfileResult*. This functor doesn't put the stream into an error
3691// state if the op fails and the profile result is non-null. Instead, the
3692// error-ness is returned in the profile result itself.
3693template <typename... Args>
3694struct ThenBlasWithProfileImpl {
3695 Stream &operator()(Stream *stream,
3696 bool (blas::BlasSupport::*blas_func)(
3697 Stream *, Args..., blas::ProfileResult *),
3698 Args... args, blas::ProfileResult *profile_result) {
3699 ThenBlasImpl<Args..., blas::ProfileResult *> Runner;
3700 bool record_error = profile_result == nullptr;
3701 return Runner.Run(stream, blas_func, record_error, args..., profile_result);
3702 }
3703};
3704} // anonymous namespace
3705
3706Stream &Stream::ThenBlasGemvWithProfiling(
3707 blas::Transpose trans, uint64 m, uint64 n, float alpha,
3708 const DeviceMemory<float> &a, int lda, const DeviceMemory<float> &x,
3709 int incx, float beta, DeviceMemory<float> *y, int incy,
3710 blas::ProfileResult *output_profile_result) {
3711 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(trans), PARAM(m), PARAM(n), PARAM(alpha), PARAM(a),
3712 PARAM(lda), PARAM(x), PARAM(incx), PARAM(beta), PARAM(y),
3713 PARAM(incy));
3714
3715 ThenBlasWithProfileImpl<
3716 blas::Transpose, uint64, uint64, float, const DeviceMemory<float> &, int,
3717 const DeviceMemory<float> &, int, float, DeviceMemory<float> *, int>
3718 impl;
3719 return impl(this, &blas::BlasSupport::DoBlasGemvWithProfiling, trans, m, n,
3720 alpha, a, lda, x, incx, beta, y, incy, output_profile_result);
3721}
3722
3723Stream &Stream::ThenBlasGemvWithProfiling(

5117 const DeviceMemory<std::complex<float>> &input,
5118 DeviceMemory<float> *output) {
5119 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(plan), PARAM(input), PARAM(output));
5120
5121 if (ok()) {
5122 if (fft::FftSupport *fft = parent_->AsFft()) {
5123 CheckError(fft->DoFft(this, plan, input, output));
5124 } else {
5125 SetError();
5126 LOG(INFO) << "attempting to perform FFT operation using StreamExecutor "
5127 "without FFT support";
5128 }
5129 }
5130 return *this;
5131}

5150// It looks confusing, but all this is doing is inserting a callback at the
5151// present point in the stream to then enqueue a task on the host executor.
5152Stream &Stream::ThenEnqueueOnBackgroundThread(
5153 std::function<void(StreamExecutor *)> task) {
5154 VLOG_CALL(PARAM(task));
5155
5156 StreamExecutor *stream_executor = this->parent_;
5157 std::function<void()> bound_task = std::bind(task, stream_executor);
5158
5159 return ThenDoHostCallback([stream_executor, bound_task]() {
5160 stream_executor->EnqueueOnBackgroundThread(bound_task);
5161 });
5162}
5163
5164port::Status Stream::BlockHostUntilDone() {
5165 VLOG_CALL();
5166
5167 if (!ok()) {
5168 port::Status status = port::Status(
5169 port::error::INTERNAL,
5170 "stream did not block host until done; was already in an error state");
5171 LOG(INFO) << status << " " << this;
5172 return status;
5173 }
5174
5175 port::Status first_error;
5176 {
5177 // Wait until all active sub-streams have done their tasks.
5178 mutex_lock lock{mu_};
5179 for (auto &stream : sub_streams_) {
5180 if (!stream.second) {
5181 first_error.Update(stream.first->BlockHostUntilDone());
5182 // Set this sub-stream as available.
5183 stream.second = true;
5184 }
5185 }
5186 }
5187
5188 temporary_memory_manager_.DeallocateFinalizedTemporaries();
5189
5190 first_error.Update(parent_->BlockHostUntilDone(this));
5191 CheckError(first_error.ok());
5192 return first_error;
5193}
